title: For Sale/Trade:  1916 Spanish Mauser chambered for 7.62 NATO
postcontent: This is my 1916 Spanish Mauser that was manufactured in the 1930s. It is based off the classic 1893 Mauser design, not as long. This partiular rifle was used by the Spanish Military and served in the Spanish Civil war. Around the mid 50s, Spain begain converting these old 7mm mauser rifles to 7.62 NATO, in order to fulfill their need of a rifle that could shoot NATO rounds. The barrel is stamped .308w however, and I have safely shot both cartridges out of the gun with no issues what so ever. It will cleanly and smoothly cycle either round. This rifle has NO MISSING PIECES, and I will include them all. The rifle has very nice bore with lots of life left, there is no significant pitting anywhere on the gun, and there is absoluely no rust. It was recently taken apart and refinished-it really runs great. I'm selling this gun because I need the money for rent, and dont hunt nearly as much as I used to and I already have too many guns to take to the range. I will be taking a loss on this rifle, given all the money I spent cleaning it up and buying new pieces. I'll only trade for specific guns. Priced at $330 but feel free to give me your best offer, I really need it.
